INSERT INTO `pokedex_entries` VALUES ('#001','Bulbasaur can be seen napping in bright sunlight. There is a seed on its back. By soaking up the sun\'s rays, the seed grows progressively larger.'),('#002','There is a plant bulb on its back. When it absorbs nutrients, the bulb is said to blossom into a large flower.'),('#003','A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower. The fragrance becalms those engaged in battle.'),('#004','From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.'),('#005','It lashesabout with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.'),('#006','It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.'),('#007','when it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.'),('#008','Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.'),('#009','The pressurized water jets on this brutal Pokemon\'s shell are used for high-speed tackles.'),('#010','Perhaps because it would like to grow up quickly, it has a voracious appetite, eating a hundred leaves a day.'),('#011','A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.'),('#012','Its wings are covered in toxic scales. If it finds bird Pokemon going after Caterpie, Butterfree sprinkles its scales on them to drive them off.'),('#013','Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.'),('#014','While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.'),('#015','May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.'),('#016','Does not like to fight. It hides in tall grass and so on, foraging for food such as small bugs.'),('#017','The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as Exeggcute to its nest over 60 miles away.'),('#018','It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.'),('#019','Its fangs are long and very sharp. They grow continuously, so it gnaws on hard things to whittle them down.'),('#020','Its rear feet have three toes each. They are webbed, enabling it to swim across rivers.'),('#021','Its reckless nature leads it to stand up to other (even large) Pokemon if it has to protect its territory.'),('#022','Carrying food through Fearow\'s territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!'),('#023','By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.'),('#024','The latest research has determined that there are over 20 possible arrangements of the patterns on its stomach.'),('#025','Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.'),('#026','Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.'),('#027','It lives in areas of limited rainfall. When danger approaches, it curls up into a ball to protect its soft stomach.'),('#028','Its claws and horns often break off. The broken claws and horns can be used to craft plows for tilling farm fields.'),('#029','Though small, it must be treated with caution because of its powerfully toxic barbs. The female has smaller horns.'),('#030','The female has a gentle temperament. It emits ultrasonic cries that have the power to befuddle foes.'),('#031','The body is covered by stiff, needle-like scales. If it becomes excited, the needles bristle outwards.'),('#032','Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening for distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.'),('#033','It is easily angered. By swinging its well-developed horn wildly, it can even punch through diamond.'),('#034','It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn as it contains venom.'),('#035','They\'re popular, but they\'re rare. Trainers who show them off recklessly may be targeted by thieves.'),('#036','A Clefable uses its wings to skip lightly as if it were flying. Its bouncy step lets it even walk on water. On quiet, moonlit nights, it strolls on lakes.'),('#037','While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.'),('#038','Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.'),('#039','It captivates foes with its huge, round eyes, then lulls them to sleep by singing a soothing melody.'),('#040','Its fur is extremely fine, and supple. The exquisitely pleasant fur conveys an image of luxury.'),('#041','It has no eyeballs, so it can\'t see. It checks its surroundings via the ultrasonic waves it emits from its mouth.'),('#042','Once it bites, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.'),('#043','During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.'),('#044','Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.'),('#045','Its petals are the largest in the world. It fiendishly scatters allergy-causing pollen from its petals.'),('#046','Growing out of the bug\'s back are mushrooms called tochukaso. The mushrooms grow with the bug host.'),('#047','A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.'),('#048','Its eyes act as radar, enabling it to be active in darkness. The eyes can also shoot powerful beams.'),('#049','The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.'),('#050','It burrows through the ground at a shallow depth. It leaves raised earth in its wake, making it easy to spot.'),('#051','In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.'),('#052','All it does is sleep during daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.'),('#053','Has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. It is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.'),('#054','It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.'),('#055','The forelegs are webbed, helping to make it an adept swimmer. It can be seen swimming elegantly in lakes, etc.'),('#056','Light and agile on its feet, and ferocious in temperament. When angered, it flies into an uncontrollable frenzy.'),('#057','It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.'),('#058','Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.'),('#059','A Pokemon that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.'),('#060','Its slick black skin is thin and damp. A part of its internal organs can be seen through the skin as a spiral pattern.'),('#061','Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.'),('#062','An adept swimmer, it knows the front crawl, butterfly, and more. It is faster than the best human swimmers.'),('#063','It sleeps for 18 hours a day. It uses a variety of extrasensory powers even while asleep.'),('#064','It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close.'),('#065','It does not like physical attacks very much. Instead, it freely uses extrasensory powers to defeat foes.'),('#066','Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it\'s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.'),('#067','Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.'),('#068','Its four ruggedly developed arms can launch a flurry of 1,000 punches in just two seconds.'),('#069','Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.'),('#070','The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.'),('#071','Lures prey into its mouth with a honeylike aroma. The helpless prey is melted with a dissolving fluid.'),('#072','Its eyes are as transparent as crystals. From them, it shoots mysterious beams of light.'),('#073','It has 80 tentacles that move about freely. They can sting, causing poisoning and sharp, stabbing pain.'),('#074','Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.'),('#075','Be careful when hiking on mountain trails. Graveler ma come rolling down the path without slowing.'),('#076','It is enclosed in a hard shell that is as rugged as slabs of rock. It sheds skin once a year to grow larger.'),('#077','Its hooves are ten times harder than diamond. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.'),('#078','Very competitive, this Pokemon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.'),('#079','It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.'),('#080','When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.'),('#081','The units at its sides generate electromagnetic waves that keep it airborne. It feeds on electricity.'),('#082','A linked cluster formed of several Magnemite. It discharges powerful magnetic waves at high voltage.'),('#083','It always walks about with a plant stalk clamped in its beak. The stalk is used for building its nest.'),('#084','A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.'),('#085','An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.'),('#086','The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick icebergs.'),('#087','Its body is covered with a pure white fur. The colder the weather, the ore active it becomes.'),('#088','Appears in filthy areas. It thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.'),('#089','It is usually undetectable because it blends in with the ground. Touching it can cause terrible poisoning.'),('#090','It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.'),('#091','Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.'),('#092','Almost invisible, this gaseous Pokemon cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.'),('#093','If you get the feeling of being watched in the darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.'),('#094','On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar\'s doing.'),('#095','As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to black-colored diamonds.'),('#096','Puts enemies to sleep, then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating only bad dreams.'),('#097','The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum in a Hypno\'s hand lull the foe into deep hypnosis. While searching for prey, it polishes the pendulum.'),('#098','It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.'),('#099','Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.'),('#100','A life-form whose identity is unknown. It is said to Screech or suddenly Selfdestruct.'),('#101','It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of \"The Bomb Ball\".'),('#102','It is often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.'),('#103','It is said that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as Exeggcute.'),('#104','It wears the skull of its dead mother on its head. When it becomes lonesome, it is said to cry loudly.'),('#105','It is small and originally very weak. Its temperament turned ferocious when it began using bones.'),('#106','The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.'),('#107','While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.'),('#108','Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.'),('#109','Its thin, balloon-like body is inflated by horribly toxic gases. It reeks when it is nearby.'),('#110','It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.'),('#111','Strong, but not too bright, this Pokemon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging Tackles.'),('#112','It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.'),('#113','It lays several eggs a day. The eggs are apparently rich in nutrients and extremely delicious.'),('#114','Blue plant vines cloak the Pokemon\'s identity in a tangled mass. It entangles anything that gets close.'),('#115','It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.'),('#116','It maintains balance using its tail, which is wound up like a coil. It may spray ink from its mouth.'),('#117','Its body bristles with sharp spikes. Carelessly trying to touch it could cause fainting from the spikes.'),('#118','Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.'),('#119','The horn on its head is sharp like a drill. It bores a hole in a boulder to make its nest.'),('#120','It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.'),('#121','Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.'),('#122','It is adept at conning people. It is said to be able to create walls out of thin air by miming.'),('#123','It tears and shreds prey with its wickedly sharp scythes. It very rarely spreads its wings to fly.'),('#124','It speaks using a language that sounds human. Research is under way to determine what is being said.'),('#125','It loves to feed on strong electricity. It occasionally appears around large power plants and so on.'),('#126','Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly amidst flames.'),('#127','Its two long pincer horns are powerful. Once they grip an enemy, they won\'t release until the foe is torn.'),('#128','When it is about to Tackle, it whips its body repeatedly with its three long tails.'),('#129','It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokemon in the world.'),('#130','Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.'),('#131','Its high intelligence enables it to understand human speech. It likes to ferry people on its back.'),('#132','It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.'),('#133','An extremely rare Pokemon that may evolve in a number of different ways depending on stimuli.'),('#134','Its body\'s cellular structure is similar to the molecular composition of water. It can melt invisibly in water.'),('#135','If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.'),('#136','It has a flame bag inside its body. After inhaling deeply, it blowes out flames of nearly 3,100 degrees Fahrenheit.'),('#137','Using the most advanced technologies, scientists finally succeeded in making the first artificial Pokemon.'),('#138','A prehistoric Pokemon that lived in the primordial sea, it swims by twisting its 10 tentacles about.'),('#139','Its tentacles are highly developed as if they are hands and feet. As soon as it ensnares prey, it bites.'),('#140','This Pokemon was regenerated from the fossil of an ancient creature. It protects itself with a hard shell.'),('#141','It swims freely through water. It catches prey with its scythe-like arms and drains the victim\'s fluids.'),('#142','It was regenerated from a dinosaur\'s genetic matter that was found in amber. It flies with high-pitched cries.'),('#143','Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.'),('#144','A legendary bird Pokemon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.'),('#145','A legendary bird Pokemon that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.'),('#146','It is said to be the legendary bird Pokemon of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flare of flames.'),('#147','Long considered a mythical Pokemon until recently, when a small colony was found living underwater.'),('#148','It is said to live in seas and lakes. Even though it has no wings, it has been seen flying occasionally.'),('#149','It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.'),('#150','A Pokemon whose genetic code was repeatedly recombined for research. It turned vicious as a result.'),('#151','So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.');
